Program: The History Hour
Title: The Collapse of Northern Rock
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/w3csv0w6
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 17 Sep 2017
The run on a British bank which signalled the coming global financial crisis, a schoolboy arrested in East Germany for writing a letter, a doctor remembers the Sabra Shatila massacre in Beirut, and a Nigerian archaeological treasure trove. Photo: Northern Rock customers queuing outside the Kingston branch, in order to take their money out on September 17th 2007. Credit: Peter Macdiarmid/Getty Images Show less